Federal University Oye-Ekiti (FUOYE) has suspended the announcement of its next vice chancellor. This followed submission of preponderance of petitions. The Chairman of the university council, Dr. Mohammed Lawan, in a statement by the institution Deputy Director, Corporate Services, Mr. Adeyinka Ademuyiwa, announced the suspension of the process on Thursday. This came as the Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU), Akure Zone, alleged foul play in the process of appointing the new vice chancellor. Lawan said the process was suspended to accommodate complaints of some stakeholders, following the submission of 120 petitions against the appointment process.